column5: Not a bad evening.  River was perfect. Managed to go 4/5.  Sorry about the cell phone pics...They are pretty weak but I was solo tonight...Camera is too tough to manage.
Nice finger......  Oh yeah, nice fish too.....good day it looks like
Awesome dude, the 2nd pic is a beauty.
love the 2nd pic as well. That's amazing for a cell phone pic!
Stay off my rock! I'm coming back to claim it next week.
i included the rock in the photo just for you even though i hooked into it standing 25 feet downstream of it...just for you jay!
Beauties Dr. S   "insert clapping emotion here" Leechman

Luc did you find that hole I was talking about? You can fish it from the high side but its an easier cast and the evening sun is less of an issue on the other side.  Great mid afternoon hole too, thats where they seem to drop into coming up or if the big hole gets worked hard.  I can't wait to go steelheading!!!

Some spinning guys were in that area for the first bit so I never got over there.  Definitely would have been relief from that evening sun.  The fish in that run were actually coming from well downstream where your line sweeps hard left into the tailout on really long drifts..
Thats very close to the spot, where it pushes left. Sun is brutal there with no leaves on the trees...
Great report as usual, the email was great.  In 7 days I am gonna get my first steelhead ever, come on waders!!!
Nice doc...Hard to beat that for a quick evening fish.... The rapids wasnt as kind but we did manage some fish bouncing spawn  TDunn

Great job! im heading out in about an hour! hopefully we can do half aswell as you did!... but unfourtunatly ill be one of those "spinning guys" lol... ill have my new bearings tomarrow around noon, then all will be good!
